<br>
One day way back when I was leading a hate raid.  I get a tell from Deavi asking if I was leading hate (at the time I didn't know who this was).  I think I ignored it the first time just thinking it was someone else trying to get in at the last minute.  I get another tell and reply yes and then he asks if I minded if they go up to do some second floor stuff.  I gave a shout in sro, most people just wanted to get up there first.  I tell him that and it was settled as simple as that.<br>
<br>
Without the calander this would not have happened.  I may have got a group up there in hate, saw that IF was up there and cancelled the whole thing.<br>
<br>
I realize that Hate is one of the raids that was said should stay on the calander, but this applies to any raid.<br>
<br>
The biggest flaw I think is calander camping imo.  However I think if people begin to realize how the calander works, it wouldn't be a problem.  The reason people do camp the calander is because of the two week rule...  I tend to wonder what would happen if there was no two week rule...</font><P><p align="center"><img
